A sewage spill at the Durban marina – which began last week and worsened at the weekend – is still being cleaned up.ADVERTISINGinRead invented by Teads
The Point Yacht Club (PYC) was one of the properties affected, and said that the problem started last week, and steadily progressed into the weekend.
The spill is reported to have affected a canal known as “Lavender Creek”.
The club’s members said that they saw faecal matter, pieces of toilet roll and sanitary pads floating in the water. They then alerted the authorities.
The water, they said, seemed "milky" and the colour of weak tea.












