Point Yacht Club business committee member Edrich de Lange describes the incident, and the action taken thereafter. Video: Kamcilla Pillay

News of the incident had been circulated to the club’s members via Whatsapp.
The message said: “Please be aware that due to pump station failures during the recent periods of rain, there has been a huge inflow of sewage through Lavender Creek, and the entire marina area was a disgusting cesspool over the weekend ... There were teams pouring peroxide and chemicals into the creek on Saturday. 
It is recommended to stay off the water until the water quality has improved significantly.”
